		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Greece, officially Hellenic Republic, is a country in South East Europe neighboring Albania, Bulgaria and Turkey. Inhabited since 7000 BC, Greece has been the birthplace of Western democracy, politics, philosophy, literature, drama, many scientific and mathematic principles, and the Olympic Games. Between 3000-1100 BC the Minoans had settled and flourished in Crete. Minoans were the first advanced culture to be settled in Europe. After a couple of thousand years, having been weakened by the massive eruption of the volcanic mountain Santorini, they were eventually taken over by the Mycenaeans from mainland Greece. The Mycenaeans introduced several advanced innovations to the rest of the Mediterranean in the fields of engineering, architecture and trading. However, the Mycenaeans vanished, after a few hundred years, by the end of the 11th century BC, possibly by the invasion of the “Sea People”.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
