				By the 8th century BC Greece was mostly independent states scattered across the entire Mediterranean. In the 4th century BC, Philip of Macedonia and later his son, Alexander the Great, united mainland Greece and conquered land all
 
the way to India. In the 2nd century BC the Romans annexed Greece. Greece became and integral part of Roman history, bridging the Roman Empire to the Byzantine Empire with their language, culture, and Greek Orthodox Church. After falling under the Ottoman Empire around 15th century, Greece finally established independence in 1830.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
