		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The Parthenon was built as a temple in Athens to honor the goddess Athena, whom Athenians worshipped in the 4th century BC. The Greeks made good use of all their temples, so although The Parthenon was a temple, it was also used as the city’s treasury. It was later converted to a Christian church dedicated to Virgin Mary in 6th century AD. The Parthenon was built mainly using marble, and even though it was damaged during many wars, it was refurbished many times and after 2,600 years later it still stands today.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
